When you call `exitTutor()`, you completely ignore your previously created student with its assigned name. The first student instance you create is not in *scope* of the `exitTutor` method. In order to use the same student you create previously, you will want to pass it to the method:

```
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int choice; 

        //Sets the student&#39;s name
        Student scholar = new Student(); // Create student 1
        Scanner nameInput = new Scanner(System.in); 
        System.out.println(&quot;Please enter your name&quot;); 
        String newName = nameInput.nextLine();
        scholar.setName(newName); // Set name of student 1
        exitTutor(scholar);
    }

    public static void exitTutor(Student scholar) {
        scholar.results(&quot;&quot;); // Prints the name of student 1, which was set
        System.exit(0);
    }
```

You can also assign the student to a field instead, but this is in most cases not what you want to do:

