I fixed this by taking some advice from https://stackoverflow.com/questions/36165151/inject-data-with-guice-into-javafx-viewcontroller 

New ServiceModule.java:
```java
public class ServiceModule extends AbstractModule {
    @Override
    public void configure() {
        bind(LoginController.class);
        bind(HoldingsController.class);
        bind(RegisterController.class);
        bind(TradeController.class);
    }
}
```

So here all of the controllers for the views are bound, and I removed all of the `@Provides` elements - turns out these are completely unnecessary, and Guice can do the necessary constructor injection without any of that.

